docs.text: when i was nine , i started buying the coolest toy figures in my local department store .

docs.text: masters of the universe was the pinnacle of what i was after for action figures : they combined science fiction and fantasy , had cool names like mekanek and stinkor and each came with its own little comic book to read .

docs.text: of course , the animated series produced by filmation remains one of the most wildly successful television products in world history .

docs.text: given the tremendous success of the toys and the cartoon ( not to mention its moderately successful spin-off she-ra : princess of power ) , it was inevitable that a production company would put two and two together , come with the result of " trillions " and make a live-action masters movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: let's be blunt : masters of the universe is a very bad movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the story is painfully dull and mind-numbingly cliched ( hands up who * wouldn't * guess he-man and skeletor take their fight into the real world ) and is acted out by either incredibly untalented actors ( dolph lundgren as he-man for one ) or good actors ( james tolkan , meg foster ) given such awful characters and dialogue that they can't help but seem terrible .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it is extremely clear that someone making the movie wanted it to be as good as star wars .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: we have the alien bounty hunters , the desert skif technology , stormtrooper lookalikes and a musical score so reminiscent of john williams that " deja vu " is too polite a term to use in describing it .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: " blatant uninspired ripoff " would appear more appropriate .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: tv fans might want to check out courtney cox ( monica in friends ) and robert duncan mcneill ( lt paris in star trek : voyager ) , very early in their careers and not doing to well in them either .

docs.text: so in the face of such mindless sub-mediocrity , is there anything to make masters of the universe worth watching at all ?

docs.text: here he plays skeletor , the villain of the piece .

docs.text: dressed in opulent black velvet robes and bearing a skull for a face , he is one part darth vader , one part emperor and two parts grim reaper .

docs.text: given this character , langella falls right into it with style and precision .

docs.text: skeletor is believable , interesting and manages to tread the fine line between being a homage to the past and startlingly original in his own right .
